# Clarify before acting

If the user's request is **not 100% clear**, stop and **ask questions** before writing code or editing files.

- Do not guess intent, scope, file targets, or behaviour.
- Do not silently pick an interpretation when multiple valid options exist.
- Prefer one or two focused questions over building the wrong thing.
- Only proceed once you are confident you understand what they want.

This applies to features, refactors, renames, deletions, and documentation changes.

When the user **skips or defers** optional work you proposed, park it in **`TODO.md`** (see `.cursor/rules/ems-todo-discipline.mdc`) — do not drop it silently.
